    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1321"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1321">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.142/321</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> for
                        Foreign Affairs</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GSE1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grey</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the British Ambassador in NT Washington</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_SRSCA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Spring Rice</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-29">
                        <hi rend="italic">August 29, 1914</hi>.</date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received in the Department of State August 29</hi>.] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>His Majesty’s Government have no objection whatever to an arrangement under
                    American control to use any ship for the purpose <pb facs="1140" n="826"
                        xml:id="pg_826"/> to which it is proposed to put the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Prince Joachim</hi>. On the contrary, they would readily and gratefully
                    agree to such a plan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">E. Grey</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
